---
// Legacy URL preserved: /services/frequently-asked-questions/ .
// Source: grooming-image-archive/services__frequently-asked-questions/copy.md —
// 15 questions (the harvest has 16 ##### headings; the 16th is the closing
// "can't find what you need?" CTA, rendered as the CTA block at the foot).
//
// FIVE OWNER RULINGS 2026-07-16 land on this page (all logged in WEBSITE-PLAN.md).
// The old FAQ and the old T&Cs contradicted each other on three of them; both
// pages now say the same thing:
//   1. Pick-up windows — a NEW third set, replacing the FAQ's (2024) and the
//      T&Cs' (2023). Rendered from pricing.json so they cannot drift again.
//   2. Ear plucking — the FAQ's absolute "we will never pluck" wins; the T&Cs'
//      "unless loose hairs come away" carve-out is gone.
//   3. Payment — "Invoice" is real but by arrangement only, not a walk-up option.
//   4. The "Adventure Dog website" shop link is DROPPED — adventure-dog.co.uk is
//      a dead Shopify domain (fails TLS, returns Shopify's 409 "domain not
//      connected"). The answer stays, without an outbound link.
//   5. The "£25 puppy groom" is REMOVED (evening ruling: a stale offer). It
//      existed nowhere but this FAQ — not in the price list, not in pricing.json.
//      The free puppy introduction stays; after it, a puppy books a normal full
//      groom priced by breed.
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import HillDivider from '../../components/HillDivider.astro';
import Faq from '../../components/Faq.astro';
import { business } from '../../data/business';
import pricing from '../../data/pricing.json';
---

<Base
  title="FAQs - The Fairy Tails Dog Grooming"
  description="Here are some frequently asked questions that many of our lovely clients have asked over the years to help you when booking your groom."
  path="/services/frequently-asked-questions/"
>
  <article data-page="faqs">
    <header class="bg-moss-900 pb-16 pt-32 sm:pb-20 sm:pt-40">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
        <p class="eyebrow text-honey-300">Before you book</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-cream-50 sm:text-5xl">
          Frequently asked questions
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-xl text-lg text-cream-200">
          The things our clients have asked us over the years — on grooming, and on keeping your dog
          in good condition at home between appointments.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>
    <HillDivider class="text-moss-900" flip />

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-24 pt-10 sm:pt-14">
      <div class="divide-y divide-cream-200 border-y border-cream-200">
        <Faq q="How often should I bring my dog in for grooming?">
          <p>
            Most dogs do best with a groom every 6–8 weeks. It varies with the breed and coat length
            of your pooch — some breeds need more frequent grooms. You can also book a bath, brush
            and tidy up between grooms, which keeps the coat in condition and limits matting.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="How long will my dog's grooming appointment take?">
          <p>
            It varies a lot with your dog's size, coat condition, health, age, style and
            temperament. As a general guide, small to medium breeds take 1.5–2 hours and large
            breeds 2.5–3 hours. We'll text you 30 minutes before your dog is ready to collect.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="How do I keep my dog tangle free at home?">
          <p>
            Between appointments it's important to brush your pooch regularly, so the coat doesn't
            become matted and uncomfortable. We recommend brushing at least every other day, using a
            slicker or pin brush and a metal comb.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="Will you give my dog treats and water on their visit?">
          <p>
            There's fresh water available for every dog visiting the salon, and we have fresh chicken
            we can give your dog as a small treat. We'll always ask your permission first — we know
            some dogs have allergies or are on strict diets.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="My dog has become matted. Can you keep it fluffy?">
          <p>
            If your dog has a few knots and tangles, we're happy to brush or scissor them out. But if
            the knots are more substantial over the body and the hair has developed matting, the
            kindest and safest thing is to give your dog a fresh start by clipping the mattes away.
            That may mean a shorter cut — but the great thing is hair grows back. With regular
            at-home brushing we can work towards the look you want.
          </p>
          <p>
            We'll always ask your permission before shaving a coat short, either when you drop your
            dog off or by calling you before we proceed.
          </p>
          <p>
            Please note we charge extra for grooming matted dogs, for the additional time needed to
            remove the mattes safely and the wear and tear on our tools.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="I've selected pick up and drop off. When will my dog be collected and dropped home?">
          {
            pricing.pickup.windows.map((w) => (
              <p>
                <strong>{w.appointment}:</strong> we collect between {w.collect}, and return your dog
                between {w.home}.
              </p>
            ))
          }
          <p>
            Pick ups and drop offs run across {pricing.pickup.areas} and are charged at
            £{pricing.pickup.journeyPrice} per journey — £{pricing.pickup.journeyPrice} to collect and
            £{pricing.pickup.journeyPrice} to drop off, so £{pricing.pickup.roundTripPrice} for the round trip. They're
            available for {pricing.pickup.eligible}.
          </p>
          <p>Please note: {pricing.pickup.nervousNote.charAt(0).toLowerCase() + pricing.pickup.nervousNote.slice(1)}</p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="What if I need to cancel my appointment?">
          <p>
            We understand the unforeseen happens and you may need to cancel or re-schedule. Please
            call us on
            <a href={business.phones.mobile.tel}>{business.phones.mobile.display}</a> with as much
            notice as possible — preferably at least 24 hours.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="Can I purchase products from you to use at home?">
          <p>
            Yes — just ask us at your dog's next appointment. We're happy to recommend the products
            we use, and to point you at what will actually help your dog's coat between grooms rather
            than whatever's on offer.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="When should professional grooming start for a puppy?">
          <p>
            All puppies must be fully vaccinated before their first appointment. The younger a puppy
            is carefully introduced to the new sights, sounds and smells of a grooming salon, the
            more confident they'll be — which makes for a far better grooming experience for them.
          </p>
          <p>
            We offer <strong>free puppy introduction sessions</strong> for a first visit: they meet
            the salon and the staff, have a good sniff about, get introduced to the grooming table,
            have a brush, nails clipped if needed, lots of cuddles and — with your permission — a
            treat.
          </p>
          <p>
            After their introduction, your puppy's first proper groom can be booked as a full
            groom — priced by breed on our
            <a href="/services/full-groom-price-list/">price list</a>.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="Can I stay and watch whilst my dog is being groomed?">
          <p>
            For your dog's safety we need their full attention. Most dogs become distracted by their
            owner being there and wiggle about trying to get close to them, which makes it unsafe for
            both dog and groomer. It's best to drop your pooch off at their appointment time and come
            back once they're finished.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're very happy to show you around the salon so you can see where your pooch will be
            groomed — <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we'll find a good time. And you're
            welcome to call at any point during the appointment to see how they're getting on.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="Do you use cage dryers?">
          <p>
            No. Every pooch is dried by hand using a stand dryer, which lets us control the velocity
            and the heat. We use stand dryers as a safety and wellbeing precaution, and for a more
            one-to-one experience for your dog.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="How often does my dog need its nails trimmed?">
          <p>
            At least once a month to keep them at a sensible length. If they're excessively long we
            recommend trimming weekly, to encourage the quick (the nail vein) to recede. You don't
            need a specific appointment for nail trimming — just call us on the day and we'll agree a
            time for you to come up.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="My dog can be aggressive when being groomed. Will you still take it on?">
          <p>
            Absolutely. Our team is well trained in handling sensitive dogs and has plenty of
            experience with it. Grooming is something every dog needs, so we welcome all
            temperaments and work to make it as stress-free as possible. If you know your dog is
            sensitive about grooming, please say so when you book so the team are ready for them.
          </p>
          <p>
            Please note we charge extra for grooming sensitive dogs, for the additional time needed
            to keep both the dog and the groomer safe.
          </p>
          <p>
            We'll call you if there are any issues during the groom. It's very rare to find an
            ungroomable dog — but if we hit a serious problem that makes it impossible to proceed,
            we'll call and agree a solution with you.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="Does a groom include emptying anal glands and ear plucking?">
          <p>Sorry — we don't offer either.</p>
          <p>
            Emptying anal glands is classed as a veterinary procedure. Many dogs' anal glands empty
            naturally, but if your dog does need it done manually, we'd advise a vet.
          </p>
          <p>
            Ear plucking is an invasive procedure which can be unnecessary and painful for dogs. We
            can trim the outer hair, but we will never pluck it. If you think your dog needs its ears
            plucked, we'd advise a vet.
          </p>
        </Faq>

        <Faq q="How do I pay for my appointment?">
          <p>You can pay:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Online when you make the booking</li>
            <li>By cash</li>
            <li>By card</li>
            <li>By bank transfer</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Payment is due before you leave the salon with your dog. If you need to be invoiced
            instead, that can be arranged with us in advance — just ask.
          </p>
        </Faq>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 rounded-3xl bg-cream-100 px-6 py-10 text-center">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-moss-900">Can't find what you're after?</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-md leading-relaxed text-bark-700">
          No problem — call us on
          <a href={business.phones.mobile.tel} class="font-bold text-moss-800 underline decoration-honey-500 underline-offset-4">{business.phones.mobile.display}</a>
          or send us a message. We're always happy to help.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-moss">Contact us</a>
          <a href={business.booking.jotform} class="btn btn-honey">Book Appointment</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
